  "texts": [
    "Consequently, considerable image preprocessing may be necessary to mitigate noise or augment contrast prior to model training (Castiglioni et al. 2021).",
    "Despite the ubiquity of polarizing microscopy within paleontology, major shifts in specimen color and contrast, which relates to the crystal lattice's orientation with respect to the preferential direction of the imaging system's polarizing fil- ters, further exacerbates issues of poor image consistency, which pose challenges towards the integration of conventional OM within DL frameworks.",
    "Scanning Electron Microscopy employs an electron beam commonly generated using a field emission or thermionic source to map a sample's surface, with grayscale values reflecting emitted, scattered and backscattered electron signal intensity.",
    "SEM image data offers surface level imaging of microfossils or macrofossil components at the nano-to sub-nanoscale, as well as their elemental composition with the use of additional detectors (i.e.",
    "energydispersive X-ray: EDX/EDS)."
  ]
